  "prompt": "Why do people always ask me where I am from?",
  "response": "People might ask you where you are from out of curiosity or to start a conversation. It's a common way to get to know someone better, as it can provide insight into your background, culture, and experiences. They might also ask because they notice an accent, or because you mentioned something unique about your hometown or country. It's usually a friendly gesture, but if it bothers you, you can always politely change the subject or share as little or as much as you feel comfortable with.",
